A HIGHLY acclaimed musical show which honours victims of the First World War is coming to Greenock. War victims show comes to Greenock A HIGHLY acclaimed musical show which honours victims of the First World War is coming to Greenock.Far far from Ypres - to be staged at the Beacon Arts Centre on October 5 - received standing ovations at a sell-out perfomance at Glasgow's Royal Concert Hall and at the Edinburgh Festival Fringe.It is written and directed by Ian McCalman, and has a cast of 25. 